race.comment: MASMELO (12) has been storming home in impressive fashion her past couple of starts, being 2.6L off the winner last start over 1400m. The rise to 1800m now looks perfect and she remains right down in the weights. Well suited here and can break her maiden. MISS GRAPHENE (6) comes back from 2212m where she was very strong late in the race, beaten 0.4L at Northam. Shaun O'Donnell remains in the saddle and he may be able to sit a touch closer from an inside draw today. Right in the mix following her latest performance. YALDA NIGHT (4) hasn't been far away in recent efforts, flying home to be 3.2L away last start at Belmont. He should be suited by the rise in trip now despite the wide draw being a bit of a niggle. Recent figures stack right up and he's expected to be in the finish. SAVVY RULER (7) bumped into a subsequent Saturday winner last start and now gets Pike in the saddle. Can go one better now. LAST MILE (9) is next best dropping back in trip.
